-- Argentine Stocks: Grupo Galicia, YPF Advance; Metrogas Falls
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2011-12-29T21:17:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/argentine-stocks-grupo-financiero-galicia-and-ypf-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index rose 1.5 percent to 2,462.63.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)   rose 4 percent to
2.86 pesos. Argentina’s largest consumer lender rose in line
with global markets, which advanced as housing and labor data in
the U.S. signaled the world’s largest economy is weathering
Europe’s sovereign debt crisis.  Other banks also rose, with  Banco Hipotecario SA (BHIP)  
advancing 5.7 percent to 1.48 pesos and  BBVA Banco Frances SA (FRAN) 
 gaining 4.6 percent to 7.95 pesos.  Metrogas SA (METR)   fell 6.8 percent to 0.69 pesos. The
Argentine natural gas distribution company has fallen 23 percent
this week after YPF SA, Argentina’s largest energy company, said
Dec. 23 it won’t exercise an option to buy shares of Gas
Argentino SA, Metrogas’s holding company, from BG Group.  YPF SA (YPFD)   advanced 2 percent to 167.55 pesos, its
highest closing price since Nov. 16. Argentina’s largest energy
company rose in line with its controller  Repsol YPF SA (REP) , which
announced today the acquisition of Eurotek, a Russian
exploration and production company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
